  <h2>About alpha</h2>
  <p>alpha is a free, open-source theme for Visual Studio Code. The interface matches GitHub Dark Default and GitHub Light Default v6.3.5 byte-for-byte. The syntax palette is designed so no single token type visually overpowers another.</p>

  <h2>About the developer</h2>
  <p>alpha is designed and developed by <a href="https://gokhangunduz.dev" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><strong>G&ouml;khan G&uuml;nd&uuml;z</strong></a>, an independent developer based in Ankara, Turkey. The project is <a href="https://github.com/gokhangunduz/alpha" target="_blank" rel="noopener">open source on GitHub</a> under the MIT license.</p>

  <h2>Design philosophy</h2>
  <p>The dark variant locks every hue to the same lightness — equal weight on a dark background. The light variant retunes lightness per hue so every color clears WCAG-AA contrast on white. Same intent, adapted to the medium.</p>
</ContentLayout>
